The paper deals with the complexity analysis of a well-known algorithm (Policy Iteration) for solving optimization problems in applied mathematics such as Linear Programming, Markov Decision Processes, and 2-player Turn Based Stochastic Games. The paper uses combinatorial matrices arising from Unique Sink Orientations to analyze the complexity of the algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper deals with optimization problems, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
